<h1><span style="align-center;"> Categories of Rebalancing Strategies </span></h1>	
<hr>
<p>Rebalancing strategies are really integral parts of asset allocation strategies. Rebalancing is essential to an asset allocation strategy (after all, if there is no rebalancing, an asset allocation would not be asset allocation any more). ValidFi's has two types of rebalancing strategies: </p>
<ul>
<li>Fixed time interval: this is essentially a periodical rebalancing strategy which has a parameter to allow for monthly, quarterly or annually rebalancing</li>
<li>Opportunistic rebalancing: this strategy tries to balance the portfolio based on the portfolio asset allocation situation: whenever an asset weight deviates too much (based on a preset threshold) from its target allocation percentage, the strategy tries to balance this asset back to close to its target allocation. </li>
</ul>
